Phase 1: The MVP (Must-Have)
Focus: A functional end-to-end loop where a user reports and a dev tracks.

1. The "Zammad" Intake (Customer Support)
Omnichannel Support: Email-to-Ticket and a simple Web Form.

Collision Warning: A simple "Agent X is viewing this" tag so you don't double-reply to a customer.

Ticket History (Audit Trail): Immutable logs of status changes (New → Open → Closed).

NextAuth Integration: Basic user login so you know who is reporting.

2. The "Linear" Engine (Bug Tracking)
Keyboard Shortcuts: (e.g., C for create, CMD+K for search). This makes you 10x faster as a solo/small-team dev.

Standardized Labels: Hardcoded Bug, Feature, Support tags.

Automated Context: Capture browser/OS/URL automatically on web reports (no more "it's broken" without logs).

Simple Kanban Board: To-Do, In Progress, Done.

3. The "Hydra" Backbone (Security)
M2M Client Setup: Basic API key management so your Beego backend can securely push reports to Traccel.

JWT Validation: Middleware in your apps to check if a report coming from a microservice is authorized.

Phase 2: The "Accelerate" Release (V2)
Focus: Automation and deep integration once you have active users.

1. Advanced Workflow
Zammad-style Multitasking: Tabbed interface inside the app to switch between tickets without reloading.

SLA Timers: Visual countdowns (e.g., "Must reply in 4h") for VIP clients.

AI Pre-Triage: Automatically suggest documentation to users before they submit.

Auto-Duplicate Detection: Flagging reports that look like existing open bugs.

2. Deep Technical Integration
GitHub/GitLab Sync: Closing a ticket automatically when a PR is merged.

Visual Pins: Letting customers click on a part of your Next.js UI to "pin" a bug report (like BugHerd).

Session Replay Link: Automatically link a PostHog or LogRocket session to the bug report.

3. Scaling & Compliance
Full Hydra OIDC: Moving from simple API keys to full OpenID Connect for all internal services.

Role-Based Access (RBAC): Granular permissions (e.g., "Guest" can only see their tickets, "Dev" can see all).